USA: Repetition Is the Mother of Wisdom · Global Voices
It is funny that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the dumbest.
When it finally revealed its Afghan approach, eagerly awaited, it was shown to be a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only does the same text use several times the words "equal to Iraq", but it also did not hesitate to use the title of the Bush statement of January 2007 for its own statement: "A new way forward".
It was he himself, who three years ago criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from the civil war, and that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences."
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful one, so that today nothing is said about Iraq in the news.
Bush's reputation did not improve, yet objectively left his successor a much more favourable initial situation than he could have expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes the miracle will be repeated.
The field captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghan operation General Stanley McCristal. He, even despite traditional subordinate relations, subjected the indecisive riflemen in the White House to harsh criticism.
He asked for 40,000 men to be able to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but he didn't think anything better, so at least he fooled the general over 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he had at least 10,000 before.
The most problematic thing about Obama's whole strategy seems to be his goal, to start withdrawing troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and to finish this procedure in three years. Obama's entire doctrine generated more questions from the answers he offered.
Many doubt that the increase will bear the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement can be reached.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing bosses every day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. After it, patriarchal tribal relations will remain.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated because of confused relationships, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "capable of action", a minimum objective of the whole operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy clashes with his voluntarism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to deteriorate and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to war to "come home soon", will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, as the Taliban will regard it as an indirect declaration of American defeat.
The latest NATO summit showed that Europeans are less and less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their constituents, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with the Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and the increased sanctions have no effect on the Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: to try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek the answers precisely when, according to Obama, America begins the triumphal withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
However, each solution like this will mean a dramatic setback for the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that there are three years left for the presidential elections, and that is why there is still much time to find another strategy, if this proves to be a total failure.
