Internet auction of crashed cars
Last October the Solera group bought Autoonline, an internet platform for the sale of cars such as motorcycles or damaged special vehicles.
The operation involved a disbursement of €59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could be extended to the remaining 15% next year.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This sales and valuation service is aimed exclusively at professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, renting companies, workshops, scrappings and professional sellers who must register before starting operations.
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, 500,000 of them in Germany.
Among its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The website currently has over 1,500 registered vendors and 4,000 experts.
3,000 ads are managed daily and about 100 new ads are included in the Spanish market every day.
