Four-step workshop budget
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identify the vehicle, look for the replacement, create a budget and generate a budget.
Ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially to convince older professionals that to a greater or lesser extent they are more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 passenger cars, 109 all-terrain cars, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it you need a computer with internet connection.
Once the model to be repaired using its frame number has been identified, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as labor price, surcharges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaWorker is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a catalogue of references.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented one does not include estimated labour times.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
